It's actually a pretty good game. So what if this game was made by completely different developers and on a different engine? It received a lot of hate because those who played Part 2 were shocked, upon seeing this marvel, that such a legendary game series had been brought to such a critical state.

Pros:
+Huge selection of cars of different classes;
+Multiple maps and modes, including zombie mode and duels;
+A choice of weather, something Part 2 couldn't boast of;
+Really good car physics (very cheaty for some cars) compared to Part 4.
Cons:
-Lack of a soundtrack;
-Presence of horribly ear-piercing car sounds;
-Possible falls through the ground or teleportation into the sky, destroying the car;
-Uselessness of the derby mode due to the lack of any damage;
- A bug with characters' coats that disappear into the texture somewhere
- Eye-searing graphics
The final score, although 4/10, wasn't as bad for me as others had said. I'm probably one of the few who completed this part completely (though what's there to complete? 50 challenges and simply tedious races to get an achievement). The most astonishing thing for me is that no one, either in Russia or abroad, has yet made a full walkthrough of this game. It's basically a slander on the game's developers.
